VICE President of Evolving Women in Politics (EWIP) Mrs. Raliat Abdulsalam has admonished women to work towards personal improvement and development. According to her, the slogan for International Women’s Day, ‘Breaking the bias’, is not against the male gender, but more about personal improvement and development of women.   Lagos keen on ensuring safe blood, blood products     NURTW leaders back MC Oluomo     We’ll sustain Buhari’s legacy, says APC…   She noted that the theme is to give women the confidence to get to where they want to without limitations, whether traditional, religious or environmental. She added that women have the knowledge, intellectual capability and ability to handle leadership roles, but lack the financial capability to sustain these roles. Mrs. Abdulsalam, who expressed her annoyance at the rejected bills, especially for 35 per cent affirmative action, said: “It is very annoying because the men formed the committee to promote the bills. It was naturally assumed the bills would sail through automatically. “These rejected bills have denied women the exposure to the political world, and since women make up a larger percentage of the country’s population, they should also partake in its law making. If women are given particular positions to occupy, it would enhance healthy competition to bring out the best.”